E. COLI EHEC - USA (07): (MISSOURI) O157, UNPASTEURIZED DAIRY SUSPECTED
***********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 11 Apr 2012
Source: STLtoday, St Louis (MO) Post-Dispatch [edited]
http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/e-coli-outbreak-sickens-two-more-victims/article_103edf2f-8b5f-54a9-9898-6e9706c5e80e.html


Another 2 cases of _E. coli_ O157 infection in central Missouri were confirmed Tue 10 Apr 2012, bringing the total to 7 people in the area who have recently been sickened by the same bacterial strain, state health officials said. The patients include a 2-year-old from Boone County who is hospitalized with complications from the infection.

All 3 patients from Boone County, including the 2-year-old, reported consuming raw (unpasteurized) dairy products, according to a county health spokeswoman. There are 2 reported cases from Cooper County and 1 each in Howard and Camden counties, state health officials said. The state also named raw dairy products as a common factor in some but not all of the patients' diets.

In addition to the 2-year-old, a 17-month-old has also developed life-threatening complications affecting the kidneys. The other patients are all adults, health officials said.

[Byline: Blythe Bernhard]

